       title="Introduction" id="Introduction" help-id="introduction">
    <p>
      DynamORM is an object-relational mapper (ORM) for interacting with DynamoDB.
      Written in Typescript with a fluent query interface, it can used perform DynamoDB operations in your node applications.
    </p>

  <chapter title="Basic Concepts" id="basic-concepts">
    <p>
      The architecture of DynamORM is basic and can be broken down into four basic concepts.
    </p>

    <deflist>
      <def title="Table">An abstract class that represents a Dynamodb table</def>
      <def title="Entity">An abstract class that represents a record in dynamodb</def>
      <def title="Model">An object that exposes an api to perform CRUD operations on an Entity</def>
      <def title="QueryBuilder">A fluent query builder for executing dynamodb commands</def>
      <def title="Container">An inversion-of-control (IOC) container for creating Table, Entity, Model, and QueryBuilder instances</def>
    </deflist>

  </chapter>
</topic>
